<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>{{title}}</title>
    {{> meta}}
    {{> head}}
    <style>
        #c4kheader {
            background-image: url("/assets/images/cb/cover/c4k_cover.jpg");
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
            background-position: bottom;
            background-size: cover;

        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="scroll-assist">
{{> navbar}}
<div class="main-container">
    <section class="page-title page-title-1 bg-dark" id="c4kheader">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
                    <h2 class="mb0 bold uppercase">CODE4KIDS Winter bootcamp</h2>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        <ol class="breadcrumb breadcrumb-2">
            <li>
                <a href="#web-track" target="_self">Intro</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="#syllabus">Elements</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="#faqs">FAQ</a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="#register">Register</a>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </section>
    <a name="web-track"></a>
    <section class="bg-white">
        <div class="container text-center">
            <!-- Title -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12">
                    <h1 class="thin">Learn to Make a Web Game in 6 Days</h1>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Description -->
            <div class="row mb-xs-0">
                <div class="col-sm-12">
                    <p class="lead">
						Learn making Web games in 6 days. Computer programming is the most essential and desired skill of the 21st  century. Whatever career one decides, this skill comes in handy, not just because it equips a student with programming skills, but also because it improves decision making. Code for Kids - Winter Camp is a special 6 day bootcamp in which kids will learn - HTML, CSS, JavaScript libraries, and will be able to make HTML websites, styles &amp; animations, and build cool games like <strong>Flappy Bird</strong>, <strong>Tic Tac Toe</strong>, etc. This course will be for the students of classes VI to X and will instill a strong foundation in Computer Programming which will help them in many stages of life.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-dark">
        <div class="container text-center">
            <a name="syllabus"></a>
            <!-- Sub items-->
            <div class="row mt40 pt20">
                <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-6 mb-xs-24">
                    <i class="icon mb32 ti ti-game"></i>
                    <h6 class="uppercase">Design HTML5 websites</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Basics of web dev - internet, browser, website, webpages, html, css, js</li>
                        <li>Using dev tools: Chrome/Firefox inspector,</li>
                        <li>Ux Design and Paper Prototyping</li>
                        <li>HTML:  Tags: Head, Title, Headings, p, button, a tag</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-6 mb-xs-24">
                    <i class="icon mb32 ti ti-file"></i>
                    <h6 class="uppercase">Styles and animations with CSS</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Styling, padding margin, border, position, selectors</li>
                        <li>Pseudo-classes, animations(basic)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-6 mb-xs-24">
                    <i class="icon mb32 ti ti-write"></i>
                    <h6 class="uppercase">Programming with Javascript</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Variables ,Using log statements, Functions</li>
                        <li>getElementById, actions- click</li>
                        <li>Loops, conditionals</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3 col-sm-6 mb-xs-24">
                    <i class="icon mb32 fa fa-file-code-o"></i>
                    <h6 class="uppercase">BuildGames: FlappyBird, TicTacToe</h6>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Flappy bird</li>
                        <li>2048</li>
                        <li>TicTacToe</li>
                        <li>Guess the number</li>
                        <li>Calculator</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    
    {{> courseschedule}}
    {{> courseenroll courseEnroll=courseEnroll}}
	<a id="register"></a>
	<section>
		<div class="text-center">
			<h3>REGISTER NOW</h3>
		</div>
		<div class="container">
			<div class="course-tabs">
				<ul class="nav nav-tabs" role="tablist">
					<li role="presentation" class="wide-tab active" id="tab-dwarka">
						<a href="#dwarka" aria-controls="profile" role="tab" data-toggle="tab">Dwarka</a>
					</li>
				</ul>

				<div class="tab-content">
					<div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane active" id="dwarka">
						<div class="container widget-container" data-widget-id='{{frame-id-dwarka}}'>
							<iframe class="payment-widget" {{#if frame-id-dwarka}}id="{{frame-id-dwarka}}"{{/if}} frameborder="0" src="{{{registerLinkDwarka}}}"></iframe>
							</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

    <a name="faqs"></a>
    <section class="bg-secondary">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-12 text-center">
                    <h4 class="mb16">FAQ</h4>
                    <p class="lead mb64">(Drop a line at admissions@codingblocks.com if you have further queries)</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1">
                    <ul class="accordion accordion-2 one-open">
                        <li>
                            <div class="title">
                                <h4 class="inline-block mb0">
                                    Who should do this course?
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div class="content">
                                <p>
                                    School kids from classes VII-IX looking to start computer programming.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <div class="title">
                                <h4 class="inline-block mb0">
                                    Will this course help if my child wants a career in technology?
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div class="content">
                                <p>
                                    Yes, it certainly will help as computer programming is the most basic skill
                                    required.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <div class="title">
                                <h4 class="inline-block mb0">
                                    Will my child be able to learn languages like C, Java after this course?
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div class="content">
                                <p>
                                    This course will make it easier for the child to apply logic to computer
                                    programming, and that will go a long way in helping him/her learn new languages.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <div class="title">
                                <h4 class="inline-block mb0">
                                    Will this course be helpful if my child wants to pursue computer engineering later?
                                </h4>
                            </div>
                            <div class="content">
                                <p>
                                    Yes, with a stronghold on basics as well as good amount of effort, the child will be
                                    able to do well as a computer engineer.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

    </section>
    <!-- Footer -->
    {{> review-course-section}}
    {{> map}}
    {{> footer}}
</div>
{{> scripts}}
</body>
</html>
